Melt butter on low heat in a small pot. When it starts foaming a little add the flour and cook for one minute until it starts bubbling stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and slowly add the milk while stirring. Keep stirring on low heat until the mixture starts to thicken.
Remove from heat add the miso and egg yolk and stir.
Let the mixture sit for 5 minutes then add 1 cup grated cheese and chives and stir until all the cheese has melted.
Add the cheese mixture to the pasta and stir well.
Add salt and pepper.
Butter the sides of a baking dish add the pasta and spread the breadcrumbs and remaining cheese on top.
Bake in the oven for 35 minutes until the top is golden brown.

text:
Chicken Stuffed Sweet Potatoes @laceybaier
INGREDIENTS:
2 sweet potatoes skin on
1 tbsp olive oil
2 chicken breasts boneless and skinless
1/2 tsp kosher salt
1/4 tsp ground black pepper
2 tbsp plain greek yogurt
2 green onions sliced
2 cups fresh baby spinach
STEPS:
Preheat oven to 375 degrees F. Wash the sweet potatoes and wrap in tin foil. Place in the oven and bake for 45-60 minutes or until sweet potatoes are cooked through and tender.
Heat a skillet over medium-high heat and add the olive oil. Season the chicken with the salt and pepper and place into the hot oil.
Cook for 8-10 minutes flipping occasionally until the chicken is cooked through and the sides are golden-brown. Once the chicken is cooked dice into bite-size cubes.
Add the spinach into the skillet and toss cooking over medium heat for 1-2 minutes or until the spinach is mostly wilted.
To prepare the sweet potato start by slicing a deep slit (but not all the way through the potato) from end to end with a knife then "crack" the potato open by squeezing the ends towards one another. It will pop right open.
Top with the spinach cubed chicken dollop of plain greek yogurt and then the sliced green onions.
#sweetpotato #recipes #healthyfood"

INGREDIENTS:

How meal prepping changed my life: @How2mealprep

Sounds funny no? It did though. Meal prepping taught me how your work ethic will determine your results. How hard work preparation determination execution & patience will be the key to your success.
In anything in life. Any job & even any relationship you constantly need to put in work every day in order to succeed in that area. If you want to be successful in your job you need to work you tail off. How do you work your tail off you might ask? You lay out everything on the table make a plan. Figure out your best way to make and Impact to see results. "earn your respect" (that's your preparation)
Determination: You give it your all! Even on days you don't want to get out of bed you go out there no matter what and motivate yourself you DO NOT allow anything to get in your way of your vision!
Execution & patience: 
Once your vision is crystal clear day in and day out you work flawlessly towards that. Don't let a bad or mediocre day ruin your sight. Everything great in life takes time. Trust the process and trust your gut. No matter what if you give it your all - its a guarantee you will be successful in that field. (If you don't believe me try it)
That's why I say that about meal prepping. Week in and week out I do this for I have a goal. A goal some make fun of or a goal some admire. Nonetheless it's a goal & no matter what - there is nothing that can stop me from achieving those results. 
#Facts

P.s you feel amazing in the process. Eating healthy gives you more energy mental clarity and motivates the hell outta ya to be the best you.

Todays tip is for Roasting Veggies:
Roasting vegetables is a great way to bring out their natural sweetness but waiting 30 to 40 minutes for each pan of nutrient-rich goodness to cook can be time-consuming. To prep a large batch of veggies try pairing them based on roasting time. Fast-cooking vegetables that can bake in the same pan include asparagus mushrooms and cherry tomatoes; slow-roasting vegetables include carrots cauliflower onions potatoes and parsnips. #mealpreptips

text:
Sunday night meal prep!!!
â© Mason jar Guideline:

Layer âŠ

The first layer in a mason jar prep should be the dressing. By placing dressing at the bottom you are protecting the salad as a whole from getting soggy! â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯
Layer â‹

Heavier Veggies.

This is an important layer it protects the dressing from "shielding" it from getting soggy.. Vegetables you can use are such as asparagus celery carrots  cucumbers red onion broccoli cauliflower tomatoes peppers and any other vegetable('s) you like. â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯
Layer âŒ

Lighter Vegetables & beans.

This layer is sort of as a second defense between the dressing and lettuce. Input â€”beans and other less heavy vegetables such as mushrooms zucchini sprouts green beans corn etc. If you are using an avocado then that would be in this layer too. â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯
Layer â

Pasta and/or grains!

Optional if using pasta and grains you can use any type of pasta rice couscous and/or quinoa. Really anything would work so you can get creative. â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯
Layer â

Protein!

Protein such as meat cheese eggs AND/or seafood! â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯
Layer â

Lettuce nuts and seeds.

In this last layer you want to put ingredients that would become soft and soggy easily if touches the dressing.. Lettuce Arugula baby spinach and field greens or popular choices. Top of with nuts and seeds such as cashews walnuts flax seeds hemp seeds ANYTHING you prefer! â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯â‹¯
There isn't a "correct way of prepping a mason jar to each their own! But this is a great guideline to base a deliciously crunchy fresh salad!! #How2MealPrep #mealprep

text:
â˜ Jan 1st 2016. 
Today like any other day can be a day for a fresh start. "New year new me" hey if that works for you then so be! But today's a new day just like tom is to make a difference in your life to better your future!

It's all about prioritizing things in your life. If you make it your motive to to have a successful day. You will do all your work make sure you go above and beyond to feel good about your day. If you make it your goal to make extra money your work hours will go into the night and you will find ways to fit it into your schedule to get where you want to be financially. If you make it your motive to be a healthier you - to genuinely feel better about yourself to be fit to have the body you want. You will get there! It's all about prioritizing. When you give 100% to things there is absolutely nothing in this world that can get in your way. If you're thinking now "that's not true" you're not being honest with yourself. You maybe giving 99% but that 1% can drag you further then you know. Whether its the body you want the car in your drive way the house on the hills.. You need to give it your all & if you give every last drop of you I promise you. You will succeed. It's the only formula to success. Along that journey will come a loss with many things that most people are afraid to sacrifice for but if you want it bad enough you will drop anything holding you back To achieve greatness. By documenting your goals on paper you're more likely to get there. It triggers something in your brain to make your vision a realistic accomplishment and not just a fantasy in your head. Fresh fruit composes tons of antioxidants! The nutrition benefits are emormous! 
When you include fruits in your daily diet you are protecting yourself from minor ailments like: 
Wrinkling of skin
Hair-fall
Memory loss 
Alzheimerâ€™s disease
Colon cancers
Weak bones & the list goes on!
